.TH "manage_rcvq" 9 "manage_rcvq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
manage_rcvq \- manage a context's receive queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" manage_rcvq
.BI "(struct hfi1_ctxtdata *uctxt "  ","
.BI "u16 subctxt "  ","
.BI "unsigned long arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "uctxt" 12
the context
.IP "subctxt" 12
the sub-context
.IP "arg" 12
start/stop action to carry out
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
start_stop == 0 disables receive on the context, for use in queue
overflow conditions.  start_stop==1 re-enables, to be used to
re-init the software copy of the head register
